title: Blue Angel practices, shows close I-90 at times this week
text:
The Blue Angels are back this year at Seafair, which means the Interstate 90 bridge will be closed several times this week.
I-90 will be closed to all vehicles, pedestrians and cyclists, eastbound and westbound, mainline and express lanes, between Island Crest Way on Mercer Island and Interstate 5 in Seattle, according to the Washington State Department of Transportation (WSDOT) website .

• Friday, July 31: 11:50 a.m. – 2:40 p.m. (Practice)
Most Read Stories Mariners’ triple play hadn’t been seen since 1955 Seattle police officer faces firing over arrest of man carrying golf club 5 things you should know about Microsoft’s Windows 10 Before getting the ax, Steve Sandmeyer show was scraping by Seattle’s Panama Hotel deemed a National Treasure • Saturday, Aug. 1: 11:50 a.m. – 2:40 p.m. (Full show)
• Sunday, Aug. 2: 11:50 a.m. – 2:40 p.m. (Full show)
The bridge highrises will still be accessible to pedestrians and cyclists.
The Federal Aviation Administration requires the closure of I-90 while the Blue Angels practice and perform for the safety of both drivers and pilots, according to WSDOT.
Seattle Times staff
